               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of ʿĀlamgīr'nāmah by Muḥammad Kāẓim ibn Muḥammad Amīn ibn Abū al-Ḥusayn al-Qazvīnī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85135483 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115921 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064913" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_689C-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_3257">ʿĀlamgīr'nāmah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_3257">عالم گير نامه</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Substantial fragment from an early copy of the official regnal chronicle commissioned by the Timurid Emperor ʿĀlamgīr I, written by <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656382.0x000001 viaf_155145541808496601063" role="aut">Munshīʾ Muḥammad Kāẓim</persName> (d. 1092/1681), son of the historian for Emperor Shāh Jahān I, <persName key="viaf_15147663108860552472" role="oth">Munshīʾ ‘Amīnā’ Muḥammad Amīn ibn Abū al-Ḥusayn al-Qazvīnī</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The annalist chronicle covers the war of succession leading to the overthrow of Emperor Shāh Jahān I, and Prince Muḥammad Awrangzīb Bahādur’s accession to the throne as emperor, followed by the first ten regnal years. 
</p>
                        <p>Defective at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Annotations. 
</p>
                        <p>Scribal nastaʿlīq. 
</p>
                        <p>Stamped foliation. 
</p>
                        <p>Lacking original binding or paper dust wrapper. 
</p>
                        <p>Folios unbound; wormholes, cropped, light water stains, smudging, creased and stained edges. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656382.0x000001 viaf_155145541808496601063">Muḥammad Kāẓim ibn Muḥammad Amīn ibn Abū al-Ḥusayn al-Qazvīnī</persName>
